<sect1><title>Foreword</title>

<para>
Following the <ulink url="http://www.oreilly.com/catalog/cookbook">Perl
Cookbook</ulink> (by Tom Christiansen and Nathan Torkington, published by
O'Reilly) spirit, the <ulink url="http://pleac.sf.net">PLEAC
Project</ulink> aims to gather fans of programming, in order to implement
the solutions in other programming languages.
</para>

<para>
In this document, you'll find an implementation of the Solutions of the
Perl Cookbook in the <ulink url="PLEAC:WEB:CAELP">PLEAC:NAME:CAELP</ulink> language.
</para>

</sect1>

